            <div class="feature-panel feature-panel--left">
                <span class="feature-panel-icon" aria-hidden="true">🚆</span>
                <h3>By Train</h3>
                <p>Cathcart Railway Station is approximately 400 metres away — around a
                5-minute walk. The following ScotRail services stop at Cathcart:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The Cathcart Circle Line from Glasgow Central</li>
                    <li>The Neilston Line from Glasgow Central</li>
                </ul>
                <p><em>Please note the Newton train does not stop at Cathcart.</em></p>
                <a href="https://www.scotrail.co.uk/plan-your-journey/timetables-and-routes"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="section-link">ScotRail timetables &rarr;</a>
            </div>

            {# Middle: Bus + Car #}
            <div class="feature-panel feature-panel--left">
                <span class="feature-panel-icon" aria-hidden="true">🚌</span>
                <h3>By Bus</h3>
                <p>First Bus services <strong>4</strong> and <strong>6</strong> stop on
                Clarkston Road, a short walk from the church.</p>
                <a href="https://www.firstgroup.com/greater-glasgow"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="section-link">First Bus timetables &rarr;</a>

                <h3>By Car</h3>
                <p>There is a small church car park (around 12 spaces) accessed via the
                lane beside the church building — approximately 25 metres from the car
                park to the front door. Additional on-street parking is available on
                Struan Road and Kildare Road, though it can be busier when events are
                on at the nearby Couper Institute.</p>
                <p>There is no designated Blue Badge parking, but the entrance is
                step-free from the car park and a hearing loop system is available
                inside.</p>
            </div>

